        "created_at": "2019-08-11T13:09:28.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"154023\">\n<blockquote>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/wine.asp?iWine=2747810\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2015 Jean-Claude Ramonet Puligny-Montrachet Les Enseign\u00e8res</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Beaune, Puligny-Montrachet (8/11/2019)</em><br>\nRipe peach fruits are trimmed with aniseed spice. It is full, rich and sappy and is a big Puligny, but possesses the usual Ramonet elegance and lightness of touch. Length is good and I\u2019ll hold remaining bottles to develop a bit more complexity.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Enseign\u00e8res was one of the successes in their 2015 range. One of the less fat, livelier bottlings.</p>",
